The paper deals with image restoration, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of total variation regularization is also a common technique in image processing and computer vision, which falls under information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new regularization method that involves group sparsity, which is a common technique in signal processing (cs.MM) and statistical inference (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV, followed by cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, and cs.SI.
